caption: Amazing ramen and service!
5* for this place
Broth was amazing. Good options for Sake. Food was yummmm.
Delicious food, excellent service, wish the omikase was more courses.
Best Ramen in Chicago
Road trip, stop by Chicago. But picked wrong restaurant. Food was normal. No customer service. The waiter was really impatient!
Superb ramen and service!

The noodles themselves were great, chewy, not too soft or too hard. The soup was also fantastic even though I am the fan of pork bone soup instead of broth. Chashu was too fat. The thickness was either too thick or too thin. The chief really need to work on his slicing technique. Karaage nuggets was the worst of the worst if you ever tried real karaage nuggets before... Last thing, we wait there for about more than an hour.. and our soup was not warm at the time it was served.
By far one of the best ramens I’ve ever had!
Nice atmosphere, the food is great.
The food is consistently well prepared and yummy, employees provides fantastic customer service. I really like how clean it is and vibes. Will visit here again.
One of the nicest Ramen Places in Fulton Market. They also serve Sushi. We had the Chicken Karaage nuggets, Spicy Chicken Paitan Ramen and Spicy Miso Ramen.

The best ramen I’ve had in Chicago hands down! I’ve tried it all and the ramen here and at their sister restaurant ramen wasabi top them all! The service was also wonderful, I loved chatting with our server and he was very knowledgeable. They have tents outside to abide by the Covid restrictions and even though it was cold outside, the tents had heaters and they blocked the wind so we were able to keep warm! Of course the ramen helped as well! Highly recommend this spot I can’t wait to come back.
I've been here multiple times and this place is consistently delicious!
Their ramen is awesome!  My favorite is the spicy chicken paitan!!  Their takoyaki is also very good!!!

(Translated by Google) Overall quite disappointing. The fried chicken has no taste at all, and the meat has been fried. It is very old and hard, with the same taste as chewing wax. The small octopus balls have also been made. The skin is as hard as the shell, and the inside is not soft, so it is unpalatable. The ramen is barely pass, the soup is okay, it's a bit salty, and the noodles are not particularly chewy. The service is so-so, absent-minded. Two appetizers and two bowls of ramen are faster than $40 per person. It is too high for this taste and service. With so many delicious Japanese food and ramen in Chicago, it is impossible to come here again.  (Original) 总体挺失望的。 炸鸡完全没有味道，肉也炸过了，很老很硬，味同嚼蜡。章鱼小丸子也做过了，皮硬得跟壳一样，里面也不松软，就很难吃。 拉面勉强及格吧，汤底还可以，咸了点，面条不是特别筋道。 服务一般般，心不在焉。两个前菜两碗拉面人均快$40。对于这种味道和服务来说实在是太高了。 芝加哥那么多好吃的日料和拉面，这里是不可能再来了。
ramen, my favorite treat. I like it here, excellent food & service. The service here is better than most.
A preferred place for Ramen. staff is always super even when they have a full house. prices are fair i would say.
The Vegan Tan Tan Ramen with egg noodles is one of best vegan ramen bowls in the city.
Ramen and the scene at this place is super good. I'll return with my relatives. Prices are reasonable.
My first choice for ramen in Chicago. The takoyaki is probably the most authentic you’ll find in the city. Small dining room, but they have a bar area, so the wait isn’t too bad.
Donburi - with pork belly was yumm. Must try - Karage (fried chicken) , pork belly buns.

The food arrived 1 hour later than the online estimate. The pork belly buns were completely cold, the food seemed to be in the container for a long time. The broth was warm. When I called to ask for an update 20 min after the estimated delivery time, the woman on the phone was giggling constantly and struggling to form sentences, she was pretty disrespectful... maybe she was high?. First time ordering from this place, most likely the last one.

The outside seated area was nice. Tables were spaced out enough to social distance from the other customers. Service was pretty good as well. Fast and helpful with suggestions. The food was amazingly prepared and delicious. I will definitely be coming back!
Slow restaurant ever
ramen and the feeling here is great. I will probably become a regular. Menu is like a cafe in Indianapolis I liked.
Ramen... so delicious. Nice place to relax, people watch, eat good, etc.  The place has a good atmosphere.
Delicious ramen in the west loop! Their outdoor patio is very nice and service was great. Still thinking about the lobster roll, it was so friggen good. Good vibes all around here
Our waitress was amazing the food a little over priced! But great vibe overall

Great ramen!!! Comes recommended by a highly rated ramen chef. If you go here, I recommend ordering the bowl in the pictures included: shio ramen with yuzu sauce in the side. It’s my second time here and not my last. I’m very careful with how much ramen I eat because you know what it does to that stomach lol. But trust me, this place is worth the sacrifice of an extra set of crunches! Grace was our server and she was a delight!  Again, I fully recommend that you check this place out for the best shio ramen in Chicago.

Very good ramen! We stepped in after checking reviews and it was actually full of people, during a Wednesday...good sign! They also have a selection of Japanese whiskey, so probably cocktails aren't bad too.

Terrible experience. Brian is condescending, disrespectful, and unprofessional. He will continually interrupt you over the phone, tell you there's nothing that can be done, and give you a quick, cold apology under his breath. Used to go here all the time, but you can bet I will not be returning so long as this lead chef continues to be employed there. Ramen Takeya, please reevaluate the professionalism of your employee.  They will leave your food out cold and promise you they're "working on it" when in fact they forgot what your order was. The worst part is that all we wanted to hear was a sincere apology for the miscommunication. But, no, Brian was too prideful to be professional and offer us that.

Good, solid ramen here. That’s for sure. No they don’t do hakata pork ramen, but you will find great miso, shoyu and other styles. It’s refreshing actually. The service was great. Fast, friendly, efficient. They have outdoor seating for these pandemic days. The vibe on the inside is great. My 東京人 will feel a bit like they’re are in an izakaya in Nakameguro or Daikanyama.  Definitely recommend 👍

This is my second favorite ramen spot in Chicago! I would come here by myself just to get my slurp on! Their flavors are well blended and the pork is delicious! I also love the garlic chips - the more garlic the better!  A great place to try if you're new to ramen.

This ramen restaurant had great good but also had great service and our waiter was very nice. I ordered the classic Tokyo ramen and it was some of the best ramen I've ever had, no kidding. The eel Don was also very good and was a great appetizer. Since I came during COVID19 they had precautions to prevent COVID19 from spreading. They had spaced out tables and masks were required. They also had hands sanitizer everywhere. 10/10 would recommend.
The food is absolutely amazing, and I can guarantee that you'll leave full, and satisfied. You can also sit outside if you want, so there are a lot of things to look at.
Highly recommend!!! Everything we order was outstanding!!!!!
Ordered ramen, poke bowls and a few apps. Everything was absolutely delicious.
Very good ramen. Better than Ramen-san.
Good food
Attentive service. Delicious food.
Last went in December. Small place but was quickly seated. Food is great.

One of the best restaurants I've ever been to in my life! We chose 3 different things (chicken steamed bun sandwich, crispy brussels sprouts, and ramen). We also got some Japanese whisky and an unfiltered sake. Everything was so flavorful and just fantastic. I can't wait to go back whenever I return to Chicago.
Excellent service, great food and drinks. Loved the scallop sushi. Can’t wait to come back!
The best ramen ever spicy miso is the way to go

We eat a LOT of ramen, and we still come back to Ramen Takeya over and over again (I generally make it a rule to try new things as much as possible, so this is kind of a big deal!). Especially now, during the pandemic, I know it’s been tough for restaurants to adapt, but Ramen Takeya has been going so far out of their way for their customers. They also take no contact really seriously and took it upon themselves to post signs allowing only one person inside at a time early on. Some restaurants we’ve tried have been a little unorganized (understandably so, but still, easily fixable issues like crowding) - but not Ramen Takeya. Even this last time they fulfilled my dream request of an extra yuzu boost (my favorite) even though it wasn’t on the menu. And the Ramen travels well and is still just as good (albeit, I still miss the atmosphere dining in). Thanks for all you’re doing and can’t wait to come back again soon!
The best ramen restaurant in Chicago

We love going out. Yesterday we  found this delicious restaurant which we didn’t know before. We enjoyed a delightful evening there with delicious meal and  an experienced stuff and a great chief cook. We put this place in our phone list  and we shall surely come back soon.  Highly recommended.
The best Vegan ramen in town, hands down. Amazing staff, great service and delicious food. The pic shows the heavy check mark :)
Hands down my fav ramen place out of all the places in the midwest!

Food came an hour late and I ordered a ramen to go. They forgot the ramen and I had to remind them twice and then I was charged for 2 additional appetizers along with the wrong ramen.  Incredibly disappointing. The food was decent but I won’t return because of how terrible the service was. They also were not busy.

Neat place with ample seating. We sat at the community table. But they seemed to turn over tables pretty quickly, probably could have moved to a private table if we wanted. My friends complained about her pork being cold, but she didn't say anything. The temperature of mine was fine, I would have liked it a little hotter. Over all delicious!
My favorite spot for vegetarian ramen
We had an excellent  at this place. We liked the superb vibes and the meals. The staff members were super friendly. I am happy we ultimately decided to visit this spot.
Great ramen. Strongly recommend.
Great chicken-based broth ramen! The brussel sprout appetizer was also delicious - loved the lemony, garlic flavor.
Fantastic food all around, plus great atmosphere.

I celebrated my graduation today in this delicious restaurant. happy to tell that it was a phenomenal evening and the restaurant was absolutely the reason for that fruitful evening. The waiters  collaborated in a very nice manner, the meals were appetizing and my guests were extremely  thrilled. We shall no dout return for more joyful events. thanks very much.

it's probably worth the money I couldn't tell. the food was very good but don't expect typical prices. they're not exorbitant, but they were expensive. they had a number of really interesting rolls by the look of it, but I was priced out.  nonetheless, we had a pleasant evening. thre service was good. the foods we got was also good. the decor is nice
This spot constantly delivers. They have excellent dishes for reasonable pricing, there no long wait even when the spot is packed.
I love this ramen shop very well!

This spot is my preferred one. I visit plenty of restaurants but here I keep coming back again and again. The team is very receptive and the cuisine they place on your table is so flavorful. I never miss an opportunity to have a decent meal in this restaurant. I highly recommend this place.
Miso bold and spicy ramen 👍👍
The eggs were marinaded beautifully. If you get spice expect spice. Great place.
Great food, kinda of an annoying hipster vibe. The staff is not very friendly, except for a select few.

The interior design is amazing. I loved everything about it. The food was great, I would just recommend getting the extra noodle option. Great use of space for a narrow location. With that being said, expect a bump or 2 when walking about or pulling out seats. Very solid business.  You can see the cooks behind glass with seating available along side it.  Wouldnt exactly go in groups larger than 4 but again, very solid spot.  Going on a date? Come here. (Dim lights & tiny candles on the tables)
Its ok
The ramen was one of the best that I’ve had in a while! Definitely recommend!
Best Ramen place in the West loop. We all enjoyed are Ramen including our vegetarians. Several of us enjoyed adding extra corn and extra molten egg. We also liked the chicken mantou buns.
This place is good I like almost everything Just not the food runner He was rude, I saw it with every table
Best Ramen in the city.

This is clearly one of the best restaurants in the area. Every time I go there I am incredibly pleased. They always keep their high  level service and the highest level of food  they offer. You will be always satisfied with this restaurant. Warmly  recommended.
Had a great experience in this spot with my kid. The food comes out quickly and the service is just good. Prices are fair.
Really enjoyed the mushroom based ramen
Excellent
So good! This is a favorite place for lunch. Food tastes great, service is pleasant. Have not been disappointed. Recommended highly.

Aside from Wasabi, hands down, best ramen in the city. Probably because Wasabi owns it 😂. Definitely recommend the karage and takoyaki. I love the miso ramen but if you're looking for something lighter, their chicken broth ramen is delicious.
Really good stuff, but the portions were not big enough. I'm not a big eater and I wasn't satisfied. I ordered the poke. That's pretty important to me and I think to most people.
The spiciness was spot on, the texture of the noodles was perfect, and the overall balance was quite excellent. This was quality ramen.

Averagely good ramen with good consistency. I've been there quite a few times for convenient and they are always at the same quality. They are not the best in Chicago, but good enough that I always go back. Eggs are cooked right. Good broth and good meat, although it could be softer and more melty. Don't get their mochi though, Trader Joe's are way better! Good amount of Japanese whiskey on the menu.
Amazing Ramen, 100% recommended
First class traditional Ramen.  Epic pork buns. Casual setting.
Delicious Japanese food especially their noodle soup with pork or chicken. Awesome!!!

If I have one negative thing to say about Takeya, it’s that they don’t do Tonkotsu. Other than that, absolutely no complaints. The food is outstanding.  They used to sell alcohol, i remember drinking a sake- grapefruit cocktail that was out of this world.  Sadly, no more alcohol according to the online menu.  Try the buns, have a bowl of ramen and the pork belly char siu and you will roll out of there, happy and ready for a nap.
Very good Ramen. Their chicken and mayo sauce is very delicious. If you’re not a big fan of pork, you can always substitute the protein for chicken. Great service and great music!

Delicious ramen.  Tight space so get friendly. Wasn't happy about the hard and fast rule of not sitting parties until all guests are there. Makes perfect sense in certain scenarios, but when 3 of 4 have arrives the table you sit at will not be different... they really made a point to make everyone uncomfortable.
Nice place. The Chicken Paitan Ramen is wonderful.

Nice ramen spot in the booming West Loop area.  A little hard to spot from a moving car due to the lack of any large signage, look for the black canvas awning.  Both the chicken and pork based broths are delicious.  If you want something lighter go with the chicken. Sister restaurant to Wasabi in Logan Square.  Not the largest interior so it gets busy as peak times such as lunch and dinner.

I've been trying out different ramen places in West Loop trying to find a new standard and went here recently for dinner.  It was very busy on a Sunday evening, so it at least seems to be a community favorite.  The menu is fairly expansive and not limited to soup.  I got the "traditional" Tokyo shoyu ramen and sadly have to say I was disappointed.  The broth is extremely light and there are limited condiments at the table to enhance it.  There were prominent vegetables and the pork belly was good, but I feel like ramen without decent broth doesn't do the dish justice.  Their broth is apparently chicken based, and I'm really surprised they didn't have a single tonkotsu option, which is what I consider truly "traditional".  Some of their spicier options might be better, but I'm not sure I'll be coming back if they don't put their best foot forward.
Excellent restaurant! Their bartenders know their stuff, and it never feels like an out of control bar.  The Ramen was exceptional, I will absolutely be going back!
A complex delicious meal in a hip setting. Feels old and new.

Small Ramen joint located in fulton market. Gets crowded during the weekends, wait time is expected. We waited for about 40 mins on saturday but it was worth it We tried spicy Paitan and Miso bowl those were really good with sake and hibiki drink. Definitely recommend!!
One of my favorite places to grab something to eat. convenient location, clean, and fantastic customer service. Keep it up!
Really fantastic ramen in a great atmosphere.
Best ramen in town. Great tasting chicken broth and amazing poke bowls
My new favorite ramen spot in the city. So good.
Delicious food - the ramen, the fried chicken. Highly recommend this place!
I'm not sure if tried that chicken before.
Best Ramen I’ve had outside of Japan
Spicy chicken broth. Perfect portion and broth to noodle ratio. Yummmmmmmmm
One of the best place to order a ramen and pork bun. I ordered a miso ramen. Chicken karage and a pork bun and both are highly recommended.
Best ramen I’ve had in Chicago so far.
great food but the service is "okay enough"
Vegan Ramen was soooo good
Good food and great setting. This time the music was way too loud. Like I have to shout to hear myself and honest it made my meal very uncomfortable.
Good atmosphere, delicious ramen.

This is one of the BEST ramen places I have tried here in Chicago. The restaurant is small and cute with outdoor seating.  We ordered the edamame and pork buns as starters. I ordered the miso bold and spicy ramen which was amazing because the broth was spicy just how I like it. The pork belly and egg was cooked to perfection. The portion is definitely filling. My boyfriend ordered the spicy chicken Patian ramen( his broth was not as spicy or creamy) but he thoroughly enjoyed it.  The service was great and food was phenomenal.
Fantastic ramen, I added mushroom and chili oil to the tokyo classic shoyo. Added an ice amount of spice and extra depth of flavor. Check it out!
The 6 year old loved it.. The brunch egg sandwich was good too!

Probably best ramen in Chicago and my new favourite outside of Japan. Good selection of meals and reasonable prices. Wait staff was really very nice and helpful with suggestions. The interior looks eye-pleasing.
Best ramen ever I highly recommend this place it blows other ramen places in the city away and the staff is amazing

Service was good as was ramen. They had around 5 options of different Ramen bases, so a good choice available depending on your tastestone thing was that they forgot to put egg in a couple of our bowls initially, but once we informed them they brought some out for us. I personally prefer my egg soft boiled and a little runny, however here they were hard boiled and cold. Otherwise was good.
The best ramen I've ever had in my life.

Ramen Takeya is the best ramen bar I have found in Chicago so far. With a great selection of food, and drinks. They have tighter seating arrangements, with some outside options with good weather. I would reccomend the pork buns with any visit.

The pork bun is highly recommended and they have generous ramen portions. The atmosphere is casual and trendy with table, bar, and outdoor seating options. Service can be a little slow, and parking is no bueno on the weekends.
The ramen and salmon crunch are soooooo heavy.... my husband and I both got upset stomach after the meal
The ramen was a above average, I had the Tokyo shoyu and the pork belly was very flavourful. Unfortunately the portions are a little small, service took awhile.

The food was too good to remember to take a picture. Very casual place but I enjoyed it. I had the Takoyaki and the pork donburi. Both were delicious. I can only recommend as a first time eater. I can't say how good they are in general. The pricing is also very reasonable especially compared to the tourist level pricing of many other places in the area.
I've had great Ramen in Tokyo and Osaka, but I have to say Ramen Takeya is greater than those I had in Japan!
I’m  from Japan and their ramen was pretty good! If you want to eat authentic Japanese style ramen, you need to go here! This place has a great ramen 🍜
Sooo good. The fried chicken steam buns were magical.
Ramen was very good and takoyaki was amazing. Service was kind but a bit careless and made quite a few mistakes. Location was nice and clean, with comfortable outdoor seating.

The ramen here is absolutely divine! The spicy chicken paitan ramen has a beautiful rich chicken broth that’s perfectly spicy (but not overly hot), plenty of vegetable toppings, a perfectly soft boiled egg, lots of noodles, and 2 slices of tender char siu pork belly. On top of that, the fried chicken buns were insanely good, and I wish I had more! New favorite ramen joint in Chicago!
Omg, definitely my top location for noodles right now!

Takeya has really great food and I love their salmon row on rice, but the parking situation in that part of town is now ridiculous. Too trendy, no place to park,  so I can no longer even venture down there.
Amazing ramen, the pork belly is like butter. The service tried to rush us to leave as my boyfriend finished his beer.
They use MSG in their broth.
Fantastic spot to have something when in a hurry. The service is prompt, prices are affordable, great ambience. Will come back again

Start to finish, our host and server both acted like our group was a major inconvenience.  Imagine the service you'd get at McDonalds if the cashier was having a bad day and was wishing they were anywhere else in the world.  Eye rolls.  Short, frustrated responses.  That's what our whole dinner felt like.  I went with a small group around 9 on a weekend evening.  We were able to get seated right away.  Admittedly, this is a yellow flag for a small restaurant in a really popular area.  They were already tearing down their outside seating.  We asked if we could be seated near the window opened to the outside sidewalk.  The host curtly told us he'd have to wipe the table down.  He stood there for a second - his body language implying that it would be a major inconvenience and that he's hoping we would change our minds.  We didn't.  He wiped the table down and didn't say a word to us when he finished.  We took our seats.  When our server took our orders, a couple of people in our group asked very basic questions - which are most popular, how spicy the dishes are, etc.  No one was dragging their feet or being pretentious.  But each question was met with an eye roll and a frustrated tone.  When our server left, everyone in the group commented on how uncomfortable we were.  The food and drinks were good.  I'd eat the food again, but wouldn't go there because of the whole experience.
The fried chicken buns are the best Asian style buns I’ve had in the city and the miso ramen is instantly top 4 best in the city. Definitely an experience to have with friends sharing plates.

(Asians?!) got SERIOUS DISCRIMINATION in this store! I'm an Asian. Me and my friend went to the store at around 2:00pm in afternoon. Since the store closes at 2:30pm, there was a bunch of empty tables in the store (yes, one 4-people table near the door, one 4-people table aside the wall and window, one last 2-people table near the window. And bar seats.) The waitress (Blonde pony hair, no glasses) saw us and wanna guide us to the 2-people table in a cold face. We expressed we wanna the 4-people one, since there is more than 1 available. However, the waitress again was cold and firmly said NO, we are RESTRICTED TO 2-people table or bar area DUE TO POLICY. I understand. So we went to the 2-people table. CAN YOU IMAGINE HOW TINY SPACE you got and HOW CLOSE the 2-people tables are? Along the window side, there were 4 2-people tables side by side. Trust me you if you got people in the neighbor tables you would feel you guys are "friends" and are dining together. They are right near your face. So we changed to the bar area. SO FAR I STILL UNDERSTOOD AND DIDN'T LEAVE, WHICH WAS A MISTAKE. Soon after we got seated, an American couple came and THEY WERE SEATED IN A 4-PEOPLE TABLE (the one aside the wall and window)!! Okay. I still tried to enjoy my meal (miso ramen is too salty and both the Char siu in miso ramen and Tokyo ramen are too fatty and smelly to eat.). Considering the privacy issue I decided not to take any photo as evidence. I believe the waitress realized I noticed the couple and their seat. She kept eye contact with the bartender. After payment, I talked to the waitress and expressed what she did is NOT OKAY and asked her why she seated the couple at the 4-people table. GUESS WHAT? She said "BECAUSE THERE'S NO EMPTY 2-PEOPLE TABLES ". Excuse me?!?! The whole store is almost EMPTY (the couple came at around 2:15pm)! And why not bring up bar areas?! And bring up POLICY?! Such a liar. I pointed it out and she couldn't say a word and just keep eye contact with bartender again. No need to say more. We left and won't come ever again. It is NOT OKAY to treat people in different races in such distinct ways!

Tried Spicy Chicken Paitan which isnt much spicy. But tasted good with all spices at right proportions. Would go with more spicier version, but afraid it might spoil the overall taste of the ramen. Service was quick. The quantity is heavy and I with medium appetite couldnt finish the dish...

The exterior of this ramen joint is so plain you would miss it if you weren’t looking for it. I was absolutely blown away how good the food here was. Their karaage is full of flavour, tender and juicy with a nice thin crispy batter. The Osaka shio ramen is phenomenal with the yuzu addon (don’t even think about skipping it), and was probably the best Shio ramen I have ever had  This one is a must-visit!  Check out and follow my feed @instantonium on Instagram if you like looking at delicious food and drinks!

(Translated by Google) Both fried chicken and ramen are very delicious. I think it is as delicious as ramen and fried chicken eaten in Japan.  (Original) 唐揚げもラーメンもとてもおいしい。 日本で食べるラーメンや唐揚げと変わらないくらいの美味しさだと思う。
I stopped by on a trip into the city. The food is amazing. Everything was so tasty. This is the best ramen I've ever had.
A favorite location for tasty ramen. Service is always super even when they have a full house. The bill was average for the menu. Menu is like a cafe in Indianapolis I liked.
A top scene for tasty Ramen. service is always excellent even when they have a full house. the bill was reasonable i would say. this place has many reviews for a reason.

ramen at this place - very good. Got there about two, it was not packed. The service was very welcoming and observant. Bring your appetite because portions are large. Food is similar to a cafe in Indianapolis I liked.
ramen and the atmosphere at this location is super good. Visited on a Thursday. It has a good feel to it.
Solid ramen. Recommend the shoyu and the salmon roe rice.
Really great ramen and Japanese food. They usually have a short wait.
100% spicy miso ramen

Loved it. Got the dumplings and some ramen. Wonderful flavors. Seating is limited. Extensive drink menu.  Staff was super friendly. Portions were huge. Casual. The dumplings were tender and delightfully tasty.

Unbelievable spot!  Their specialty is a chicken-focused broth but have multiple delicious choices.  My favorite dish was not the ramen but actually the pork belly char siu bun, which came with japanese mayo and romaine.  The braised Berkshire pork belly was PERFECTLY tender and I didn't even want to chew because there was so much flavor to soak in.  Honestly, probably one of the best dishes I've had all year.  The fried chicken with spicy mayo was also delicious.  The gyoza comes with the same pork and is delicious, and the miso vinaigrette adds great acidic and umami flavors.  I would go with the buns though if there was a choice.
It's on automatically Japanese food at Chicago
I would eat another bowl if I can. I love the taste of the food and the stylish atmosphere here.
Good food, nice clean room, quick service
Bar seating was perfect for a quick bite to eat! Enjoyed ramen and the poke bowl.
Great!
Enjoy the environment very much. the Ramen is good, and I especially like the rice dish they got.
Good springy noodles, but their spicy ramen was not spicy at all.
Ramen was great! Although the order took a while to get.
Simply the best, better than all the rest.

The only reason I docked this place a star is that it's never been less than sardine-can crowded, and that means you'll be waiting for a good long time. But the wait is absolutely worth it. Not quite as good as Kizuki, but they're close, and how can you dislike a place that has Gyoza so fresh that the wrapped around each piece hasn't been separated yet?
I had the vegan ramen and it was the absolute best!!!
First guest to come in and last to get food. Food over priced and service was horrible.
Excellent scene for ramen. food was super flavorful.

Ramen takeya is always a great weekend stop for us. The ramen is amazing and in my opinion probably the best in town. The service lately has been not  very up to par but I'm hoping it's due to the many new faces hired.

First time coming here after leaving the "Days Gone" event, I got the Spicy Chicken Paiten, it was my first time having a chicken based broth since most ramen places do a pork based one. It was very thick & it had a nice kick of spice after every slurp. The chashu was soft & fatty. The noodles were thin but they felt thick as I bit through them. The place is small but cozy, I really enjoyed the atmosphere. They had all types of whiskey from Japan, & some signs hanging in the hall, almost making it seem like a street market. Will probably come back to try the Miso for sure.
Had the two vegan options available, which were great and delicious. Not 5 star, since there were only 2 options, and portion sizes seemed smaller/more expensive than other asian or ramen spots.
Best ramen place in all of Chicago, go here if you want good authentic ramen
Good but soup should be more salty and darker.
Great for lunch, opens up to have an indoor/outdoor feel for when it’s nice out. Delicious ramen! 🍜
Chicken paitan ramen is so good here!
I've had Ramen Takeya 5 or so times and they have yet to disappoint.
Excellent service and the ramen was phenomenal. Clean flavors, great noodles, tons of flavor. Seats go fast, but it's worth waiting.
Good ramen but super busy place.  It is small so be prepared to have to stand and wait for a bit
My preferred place for tasty ramen. Food with real quality ingredients.  Nothing but great experiences here.
Great place for delicious ramen. The staff was very kind and attentive. This place has a cool design. Feels similar to a restaurant in New York I liked.
Great ramen and poke. I like the paitan.
Broth is great. Soft-boiled eggs done right. Tender pork. Nice atmosphere. Love it.

Small Ramen restaurant. The side dishes were amazing, especially the brussels sprouts and the pork belly bao. We were disappointed in the ramen. We had the Chicken Paitan and the Spicy Chicken Paitan and neither of them had a strong flavor. Also, their lack of a tonkotsu was disappointing as that's my personal favorite kind of ramen. The chicken bone broth just doesn't get the same flavor in my opinion.  The reason for the 2-star rating is because the staff was extremely indifferent to patrons. The hosts didn't welcome anyone at the door and it took a while to even get someone to put our name on the list. They also had a line waiting and a slow turnaround on tables. The restaurant wasn't understaffed, the servers and hosts were just showed no urgency to move the crowd at the door to tables quickly as they became available.
Best ramen ever. Chicken paitan is delicious and the brussel sprouts!!

Ramen takeya is one of my favorite ramen places in Chicago. If you love wasabi ramen you will love ramen takeya. They also have great poke bowls and other served over rice dishes. The restaurant is small however there havent been many times that I've had to wait. They also have a bar where you can grab some great Japanese whiskey while you hangout or during dinner.

LOVE THIS PLACE!! This is my #1 go-to ramen spot. The staff, atmosphere, and food is amazing! It’s decently priced and worth every penny. They really know what good ramen is all about!

One of the best spots in Chicago for Ramen. I get the spicy chicken paitan and I find myself thinking about it at home, the next day, and a week after that. It’s that good. If you have the cash, dish it out on appetizers and drinks. All the recommendations I’ve been given so far were solid, the staff is super chill and friendly, and the atmosphere brings me back to my days in Tokyo.

Delicious simple ramen! The broth has good flavor and it’s not overwhelming in flavor. The meat is very tender and compliments the broth very nicely. Would definitely come again! The place is quite small but large compared to other Japanese restaurants. It is a little misleading thought because there is no sign outside that says Takeya. Service is also good!

I came here from out of state and heard great things. However, the day I went there the restaurant had NO chicken at all. The ramen noodles also tasted Days old. They also took a very long time to get our food even though it was a weekday and day time. Very disappointed.

Truthfully I'm not quite sure why this spot is so highly rated - the interior was really nice and the service was fine, but the ramen is completely forgettable. The shoyu broth is weak in colour and flavour, and pretty much just tastes like bamboo shoots once they're added. The egg was over-marinated and tasted like soy sauce (picky, I know, but it's not hard!), and it had spinach in it, which is a terrible idea, imo. Fwiw the noodles were definitely quality. I'd love to come back to try tonkotsu or miso but unfortunately they don't sell either (the only miso is super spicy). Overall very disappointing.

My favorite place for ramen. I feel like a lot of ramen places in Chicago are fusion or not authentic Japanese. Ramen takeya is different - their ramen actually makes me miss Japan. My favorite is the soicy chicken paitan ramen, which has the perfect amount of spice along with its light broth.  I also recommend their hanetsuki gyoza and their Brussels sprouts!  If you're craving a drink try the calpico cocktail which is similar to a calpico sour you can get in Japan.
Good food, great service, and a good ramen place in Chicago!

It was rather confusing trying to find this place especially since it has no exterior signs. The place was packed.. Once we ordered our dishes looked just as we expected. Savory, spicy and full of flavor. The only drawback was the small portions.

Great first time experience. Was brought in by my sister's recommendations, service was friendly and attentive.  Ramen were pretty legit, makes you want to have it daily. Small but quaint area. Definitely plan on returning to try other dishes.
If you're going for lunch get there around 11:30 because it fills up fast

I did not enjoy my service. First of all, I asked for a green tea while pointing at the tea on the menu. I never received my tea and my server didn't care to ask how we were doing. Second, either the server messed up my ramen order or the menu is misleading, because I ordered a bowl of ramen with an EXTRA egg (thinking I would get two full eggs). When my ramen came, I only had two halves of an egg (aka, one egg). I don't know if this place only gives HALF an egg with their regular orders, but if they do, their menu is misleading and should be changed. Otherwise, the server might have forgotten to bring me an extra egg, which is also disappointing. That, along with a VERY small piece of pork belly in my ramen, made me incredibly disappointed with how stingy this restaurant is with their servings. And, finally, they added a 20% gratuity to our bill even though we were only five people (and not six)! I ended up paying waaay too much extra for amateur service. The only reason I gave two stars instead of one is because of the lightning speed of the service. But speedy does NOT always entail higher quality of food, especially since they skimp on their egg and pork belly portions. If the general manager from Ramen Takeya would like to reach out to me and explain why they were so stingy with their egg and pork belly servings in my ramen, why they forgot my tea, and why they charged 20% gratuity, I would be open to hearing from you. Otherwise, consider this negative review on every website I can imagine.

This is tops in Chicago for anybody looking for a warm, flavorful bowl of chicken ramen broth. These folks are masters of the chicken, and for once, somebody doesn’t kill me with salt.  Try the chicken karaage, which are basically Japanese chicken nuggets in a bun. A bit of sriracha mayo to top it off, and very juicy. The ramen here is excellent. It’s uncomplicated, and hits the mark in flavor and quantity.  No gimmicks or fusion this and that here. You feel like you’re in a Japanese alley at a ramen stall when you’re here. The interior is small, but they captured the tone perfectly.  Service was friendly and it didn’t seem to take long for our food. Awesome little place that I don’t mind recommending to friends.

Takeya is a really fun restaurant with a great atmosphere and solid food. I’ve been in twice and had a positive experience both times. Their buns are absolutely delectable, they have Asahi on tap, and they have a lot of bar seating, which makes it a great place to walk in casually.  The Miso Bold & Spicy ramen is my favorite here. It honestly doesn’t pack a ton of heat so don’t be afraid to order this one if you’re not into super spicy food. The broth is chicken-based, but it still has a creamy and rich quality. There was enough fatty opacity to it for me to come back even though I tend to go for the richest and spiciest pork broths.  They have a lot of bigger tables here, so if you have a group of 6 or 8 they can likely seat you all together. Just know they absolutely will not seat you unless your entire party is present. I have seen people waiting on the rest of their groups both times I walked in. My most recent visit was on a Friday night at around 7:15, and despite it being peak time my wife and I got a seat within 15 minutes. It’s definitely always busy, but not swamped.
Very good food.
Great bowl of miso ramen, char suii was delicious and broth was spicy but well balanced. Ambiance was very cozy, I ate at the counter by myself but was perfectly comfortable. Would visit again!

Would definitely come back again.

Omakase Takeya is located below Ramen Takeya. The moment you walk in, you'll check-in and then be escorted downstairs into the intimate setting for the evening. When you enter, you'll be presented with a seven seat sushi bar with head sushi Chef, Sasaki-san. Once seated, you'll be shown the items for your omakase experience, inside a carefully placed wooden box. Once your drink order has been placed, the festivities begin. A full disclaimer to those looking to dine here: Omakase Takeya is edomae style, which is very traditional. There's no frills or thrills that you should be expecting. The fanciest of items you may be presented for the evening would be a apple wood chip smoked sashimi. Aside from that, it's all very natural flavoring of the fish. There were things that I liked more than others, but nothing was bad. I was hoping for more fish (more nigiri/sashimi), instead, I was presented with almost half the menu from the kitchen (which isn't necessarily bad, I just prefer more fish than cooked items).
Food is great, but it's pretty small and you always have to wait just a little too long.

Best ramen in the city. Better than high five ramen, and without the horrendous wait. The fried chicken buns and the miso bold and spicy ramen is perfectly balanced. As someone who loves spicy food this has just enough heat to make you keep digging in for more.

Good atmosphere, great service and excellent ramen. The miso bold & spicy has just the right amount of spice with great flavor and crazy tender pork.

Best in Chicago! On par with yokohama and most tokyo and kansai ramen shops in japan!  Now adays numerous ramen shops dont use "real" broth in their soup, because i know some restaurant suppliers uses chemical solvents to make their soup more appetizing. And takeya does not. Since the broth is the soul of a ramen bowl, its paramount to have an authentic soup making process like using real and fresh ingredients.  Uni Tuna Toro Donburi 10/10 points, even though they did not use the best hokaido uni, but California uni is rated the top, with the fatty emulsion of tuna belly and freashly grinded wasabi, this bowl makes me feel like i am in japan Tsukiji market!!!  Last visit i tried the soup base chicken paidan ramen was good, but this time the Tsukemen even did better in contrast of the noodle and soup itself! Its worth 9/10 points.  And pork belly bun is also good with 8/10 points.

Arguably the best Ramen in Chicago. Also check out Ramen Wasabi (Takeya's sister restaurant). Takeya specializes in a chicken paitan broth, whereas Wasabi has the traditional pork based broth, note both styles of broth are available at takeya (although wasabi has amazing sushi). Takeya also helped introduce me to fine Japanese whiskeys and their kegerated asahi extra dry pairs excellently with everything on the menu. Their appetizers are all amazing as well. I could not recommends either restaurant more highly. Thank you satoko!

I have called about 10 times to order takeout and have only successfully gotten takeout 4 times. Its honestly very frustrating.
